<paragraph xmlns:gate="http://www.gate.ac.uk" gate:gateId="0" gate:annotMaxId="222">Aerts (ahrts), Egide, Belgian flutist; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="220" RE="March 1, 1822" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="216" predict="birth">b.</Birth> Boom, near <Location gate:gateId="180" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Antwerp</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="181" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">March 1, 1822</Date></Event_Birth>; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="221" RE="June 9, 1853" Pred="death" Pred-tyoe="time"><Death gate:gateId="217" predict="death">d.</Death> <Location gate:gateId="182" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Brussels</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="183" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">June 9, 1853</Date></Event_Birth>. A precocious musician, he studied as a child at the Brussels Cons.; gave a concert in <Location gate:gateId="185" rule1="InLoc1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Paris</Location> at the age of 15. In <Date gate:gateId="186" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1847</Date> he was appointed teacher of flute at the Brussels Cons. He wrote numerous works for flute, most of which remain in manuscript. </paragraph>